                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21830">Qiṣṣah-'i Sanjān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21830">قصهٔ سنجان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Qiṣṣah-i Sanjān, the traditional story of the settlement of the Parsis in India originally composed in verse by Bahman ibn Kayqubād ibn Hurmuzyār Sanjānī at Nausari in AD 1600.</p>
                        <p>Copy made for Burjorjee Sorabjee Ashburner from a defective copy belonging to Ghulām Muḥammad Panjābī.</p>
                        <p>Copy dated 4 Ṣafar 1281 (9 July 1864).</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_61307134">Kayqubād, Bahman</persName>
